OL,6,FAdenomyosis has been officially
OL,7,Frecognised by NHS Wales following an
OL,8,FITV Cymru Wales report.
OL,10,FSymptoms of the painful menstrual
OL,11,Fcondition, where the lining of the
OL,12,Fwomb or uterus starts growing into the
OL,13,Fmuscle of the womb, can include heavy
OL,14,For prolonged periods, severe cramping,
OL,15,Fchronic pelvic pain, bloating and pain
OL,16,Fduring intercourse.
OL,18,FOn average, it takes between seven and
OL,19,F10 years to diagnose adenomyosis,
OL,20,Fwhile it affects one in 10 women.
